                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400106-name-664" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400106-name-664" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400106-name-664" type="surname" value="CALVERT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400106-name-664" type="given" value="RICHARD ISAAC"></interp>RICHARD ISAAC CALVERT.</persName>
                  </hi>I live with Mr. William Goodburn, a pawnbroker, at Islington. On the 7th of January, between four and five o'clock in the evening, I was standing behind the counter, and heard a rustle of silk at the door—I looked, and saw the prisoner with this cloak, rolling it up, and making off with it—I went out—a lady told me he had dropped it—the prisoner walked away—I ran and took him, and gave him in charge—this is the cloak—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it</hi>.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q</hi>. Did you see me take it? <hi rend="italic">A</hi>. No; I saw you with it in your hand—you were then at the door-post—you were four doors off when I took you—you dropped the cloak before you got half-way past the window.</p>
